- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is also likely as the paper deals with the concept of abelian periods, which is related to the algebraic properties of words and languages.
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper mentions the time and space complexity of the algorithm.
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial properties of words and substrings.
- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the concept of runs, which is related to the geometric properties of words and strings.
